Sentencas: In this study, the microstructural modification of pulsed laser deposited La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-delta (LSC64) thin-film cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) to improve the lateral conduction and to reduce the surface composition degradation is investigated.
Titulo: Microstructure refinement of pulsed laser deposited La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ thin-film cathodes for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: A high-temperature deposited 100 nm-thick denser LSC64 layer is added over 2.4 mu m-thick porous cathode to cover and bridge the cathode domains.
Titulo: Microstructure refinement of pulsed laser deposited La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ thin-film cathodes for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: According to the cell performance analyses using current-voltage-power measurements, the performance of the cell modified with an additional denser layer is increased compared with the cell without the denser layer in all operating temperature range.
Titulo: Microstructure refinement of pulsed laser deposited La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ thin-film cathodes for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The degree of improvement of peak power density is bigger than 10% at 650-550 A degrees C and is about 6% at 500 A degrees C.
Titulo: Microstructure refinement of pulsed laser deposited La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ thin-film cathodes for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: This performance enhancement can be attributed to the electrochemical property improvement, especially oxygen surface exchange property, rather than to the conduction improvement, based on the electrochemical impedance analysis.
Titulo: Microstructure refinement of pulsed laser deposited La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ thin-film cathodes for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Improved crystallinity and composition integrity of the denser LSC64 layer is considered to enhance the surface exchange property of the cathode.
Titulo: Microstructure refinement of pulsed laser deposited La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ thin-film cathodes for solid oxide fuel cell
